rmc-book-text-space-grunts = {"                        "} [mono][bold][color=black][head=1]SPACE GRUNTS v2[/head][/bold][/mono]
    {"                                   "} [head=3]A game for 1-4 players[/head]

    {"["}italic]Picture of two "space grunts" shooting at air[/italic]

    This is a tabletop game you and friends can play with a standard deck of 52 cards, and a D20. You will also need some way of keeping notes and tracking points.

    You play as an elite fighting force of [bold]SPACE GRUNTS[/bold] in a battle of survival against ravenous [bold]XENOBUGS[/bold] infesting the cosmos. Create a character, and the cards generate a battle. Dice rolls determine combat. Cards are collected for bonuses and placed into a discard pile when used.

    If you're playing by yourself, you draw cards until you defeat a [bold]BOSS[/bold]. If more than one person is playing, you draw until you defeat a number of bosses equal to the [bold]number of players[/bold]. So if there are [bold]two players[/bold], you play until you fight [bold]two bosses[/bold].

    {"["}head=3][bold]Enlist in the Space Grunts[/bold][/head]
    Choose a cool name (and nickname) for your grunt and then distribute [bold]15 points[/bold] between two stats: [bold]RUN[/bold] and [bold]GUN[/bold]. Each [bold]stat[/bold] should have [bold]at least 5 points[/bold].

    {"["}bold]RUN[/bold] determines how fast a grunt is and how well they avoid [bold]attacks[/bold] and [bold]traps[/bold]. Lower numbers are better.

    Each grunt starts with [bold]3/3 HIT POINTS[/bold] and [bold]1/1 ARMOR POINT[/bold].

    Each time you receive [bold]damage[/bold], you lose an [bold]Armor Point[/bold]. When you have no armor left, each point of damage removes a [bold]Hit Point[/bold]. When you have no hit points left, you are [bold]dead[/bold] and your collected cards go into the [bold]discard pile[/bold].

    {"["}head=3][bold]Starting a Game[/bold][/head]

    {"["}italic]Picture of a 3 of clubs and a 10 of spades[/italic]

    Begin your mission by drawing a card from the deck.

    {"["}bold]Cards 3 - 10[/bold] are [bold]Xenobug Swarms[/bold]. They have a [bold]RUN[/bold] equal to their [bold]Card Number[/bold]. Swarms deal [bold]1 damage[/bold] when attacking. Their [bold]Hit Points[/bold] are equal to the [bold]number of players[/bold].

    {"["}head=3][bold]Who shoots/bites first?[/bold][/head]
    Grunts and xenobugs act in order of who has the [bold]lowest RUN[/bold]. If there is a tie, roll dice for the lowest number to determine a winner (someone rolls for the xenobugs if necessary).

    {"["}head=3][bold]Shooting and Looting[/bold][/head]

    On their turn, [bold]players[/bold] roll their [bold]GUN[/bold] score or [bold]ABOVE[/bold] to land a hit. If they do, they deal 1 point of damage. On the [bold]xenobugs turn[/bold], all players roll their [bold]RUN[/bold] score or [bold]ABOVE[/bold] to dodge the xenobug attacks. If the players fail, they receive 1 point of damage.

    {"["}italic]Picture of a bug-like alien[/italic]

    Whomever wipes out the swarm takes the card. Each swarm drops loot depending on their suit. Place collected cards into the discard pile to redeem their loot. The kind of loot is determined by the suit.

    {"["}head=3][bold]Xenobug Loot Cards to Collect:[/bold][/head]
    ♣ [bold]Clubs[/bold]: [italic]A cache of war drugs.[/italic] Add [bold]+3[/bold] to a [bold]RUN[/bold] roll.
    ♦ [bold]Diamonds[/bold]: [italic]Armor plates.[/italic] [bold]Restore 1 Armor Point.[/bold]
    ♥ [bold]Hearts[/bold]: [italic]First aid kit.[/italic] [bold]Restore 1 Hit Point[/bold] for [bold]you[/bold] or a [bold]fellow[/bold] grunt.
    ♠ [bold]Spades[/bold]: [italic]Stack of ammo.[/italic] Add [bold]+3[/bold] to a [bold]GUN[/bold] roll.

    {"["}head=3][bold]Acid Splash and Slime Pits[/bold][/head]

    {"["}italic]Picture of a 2 of clubs[/italic]

    {"["}bold]Number 2 cards[/bold] are [bold]Traps[/bold]. When one is drawn, all players roll their [bold]RUN[/bold] score or [bold]ABOVE[/bold] to dodge the trap. Players who fail discard a card they own of that suit.

    If they own no cards of that suit, they lose [bold]1 armor point[/bold]. If they have no armor, they lose [bold]1 hit point[/bold].

    Trap descriptions for flavor:
    ♣ [bold]Clubs[/bold]: [italic]Noxious slime pools threaten to dissolve you.[/italic]
    ♦ [bold]Diamonds[/bold]: [italic]Concealed acid pocket erupts violently.[/italic]
    ♥ [bold]Hearts[/bold]: [italic]A grisly parasite latches on tenaciously.[/italic]
    ♠ [bold]Spades[/bold]: [italic]Damaged equipment explodes/electrocutes.[/italic]

    {"["}head=3][bold]Rescue Hapless Civilians[/bold][/head]

    {"["}italic]Picture of a king of clubs[/italic]

    {"["}bold]Face cards[/bold] represent [bold]cocooned civilians[/bold]. They repay the grunts with a [bold]permanent bonus[/bold]. Write the bonus down and discard the card.

    The players can decide who gets the bonus or they can [bold]fight over it[/bold]. To tussle over the goods, each player rolls their [bold]GUN[/bold] score or [bold]ABOVE[/bold] until only one succeeds. The winner takes the bonus.

    {"["}head=3][bold]Civilian Loot Cards:[/bold][/head]
    ♣ [bold]Clubs[/bold]: [italic]You rescue a surgeon who modifies you with Combat Implants.[/italic] Add [bold]+1[/bold] to all [bold]RUN[/bold] rolls.
    ♦ [bold]Diamonds[/bold]: [italic]You rescue an engineer who modifies your standard armor with an upgrade.[/italic] Increase your max [bold]Armor Points by 1 (and restore all Armor Points).[/bold]
    ♥ [bold]Hearts[/bold]: [italic]Your rescue a medical researcher who boosts your robustness with gene modifcation.[/italic] Increase your max [bold]Hit Points by 1 (and restore all Hit Points).[/bold]
    ♠ [bold]Spades[/bold]: [italic]You rescue the armory master who grants you access to weapon upgrades.[/italic] Add [bold]+1[/bold] to all [bold]GUN[/bold] rolls.

    {"["}head=3][bold]Defeat the bosses![/bold][/head]

    {"["}italic]Picture of an ace of clubs[/italic]

    {"["}bold]Ace[/bold] cards represent [bold]BOSS xenobugs[/bold]. They are like swarms but they always go first in combat. Their [bold]Hit Points[/bold] are [bold]2 plus the number of players[/bold].

    Each [bold]BOSS[/bold] has its own special attack:

    ♣ [bold]Clubs[/bold]: [italic]A giant slithering monstrosity squelching with reeking slime.[/italic] This [bold]BOSS[/bold] deals 1 damage but every time it hurts a grunt, it adds 1 to their [bold]RUN score[/bold] until the end of combat.

    ♦ [bold]Diamonds[/bold]: [italic]A towering insectoid with scythe-like claws to rend armor like butter.[/italic] If this [bold]BOSS[/bold] lands a hit, it removes all [bold]Armor Points[/bold] on a grunt and deals 1 damage regardless. Ouch!

    ♥ [bold]Hearts[/bold]: [italic]A bloated crawling horror buzzing with mutant gadflys.[/italic] This [bold]BOSS[/bold] deals 1 damage but every time it hurts a grunt, it removes 1 point from their max [bold]Hit Points[/bold] until the end of combat.

    ♠ [bold]Spades[/bold]: [italic]A gargantuan insectoid belching toxic spore clouds which cloud the mind.[/italic] This [bold]BOSS[/bold] deals 1 damage but every time it hurts a grunt, it adds 1 to their [bold]GUN score[/bold] until the end of combat.

    {"["}italic]Picture of a nuclear explosion[/italic]

    {"["}bold]BOSS[/bold]es drop an [bold]ORBITAL STRIKE BEACON[/bold] as [bold]loot[/bold]. A player can redeem this card [bold]during their combat turn[/bold] to deal [bold]3 damage[/bold] instantly on a xenobug swarm or [bold]BOSS[/bold]. Xenobugs defeated this way [bold]do not drop loot[/bold] and their card directly goes into the discard pile.

    {"              "} [head=3][bold]Good luck Space Grunts! You'll need it![/bold][/head]

    {"["}head=3][bold]Common Questions:[/bold][/head]

    {"["}bold]When can I use a loot card?[/bold]
    Since ♣ [bold]Clubs[/bold] and ♠ [bold]Spades[/bold] are used for [bold]RUN[/bold] and [bold]GUN[/bold] rolls respectively, you can only use those during [bold]combat[/bold]. You can use ♦ [bold]Diamonds[/bold] and ♥ [bold]Hearts[/bold] [bold]anytime[/bold].

    {"["}bold]Can I give a card to a fellow player?[/bold]
    That's up to [bold]you[/bold]. There are no hard rules for sharing loot cards. [bold]Civilian loot cards are not to be shared[/bold]. They go immediately to the discard pile and the player who earned the bonus writes it down as a permanent part of their character.

    {"["}bold]Do we hurt each other when we fight over bonuses?[/bold]
    No, grunts [bold]deal no damage[/bold] to each other this way.

    {"["}bold]Isn't it possible to fight a boss on the first draw? Or fight bosses back to back?[/bold]
    You bet. Some games will be harder than others. That's the magic of a randomly generated game!

    {"["}bold]Can't we just make up our own rules[/bold]
    Play the way you and other players want to. Have fun!

    {"["}italic]Picture of a helmet-wearing skull with a worm-like bug crawling out[/italic]

